<TEXT>
an unidentified japanese bidding by telephone paid 
an auction record price of 609 million for a work by artist marc 
chagall 
the 1949 painting by the russianborn artist the bride under 
the canopy was the highestpriced work in tuesday nights sale 
at sothebys of impressionist and modern art 
chagall painted the bride under the canopy after he returned 
to france from the united states 
it shows a bride and groom under an awning with a large vase of 
leaves and flowers and a violinist one of chagalls lucky 
charms 
another chagall of a vase of flowers with russian people and 
motifs around the edges the farmers bouquet went for 502 
million the buyer also was a japanese telephone bidder 
sothebys did not say if the two chagalls went to the same buyer 
anonymous japanese also paid 35 million for a 1933 work by 
paul klee arrival of the bridegroom and the same price for a 
pablo picasso 1904 blue portrait of the catalan poet jaime sabartes 
sabartes became picassos secretary and he wrote a biography of 
the artist in 1946 he also collaborated with wilhelm boeck on a 
comprehensive study of picassos art published in new york in 1955 
