<TEXT>
evidence of test buying and other cheating has 
led the educational testing service to cancel the scores of some 
6600 students in india who took the graduate record examination 
between october and february 
in the wake of what is almost certainly the worst case in 
history of cheating on standardized tests ets said monday it will 
offer the exams less often and at fewer locations in india 
a fivemonth investigation found security breaches at many test 
centers and evidence students had been able to buy copies of the 
exam in advance 
the problems came to light in december when the princeton 
njbased test service said it was wiping out the scores of 2744 
indian students who took the gre in october the test is for 
admission to graduate school 
ets spokesman ray nicosia said at that time that the test 
service had received dozens of letters from indian students and 
test center supervisors indicating that students had been able to 
buy copies of the test beforehand 
the test administered to some 366000 students worldwide each 
year is taken by 14000 indian students 
the cheating continued despite the investigation said charlotte 
kuh ets executive director of gre programs 
she said the service canceled the scores of students who took 
the gre on jan 20 feb 3 and feb 10 bringing the number of 
cancellations to about 6600 
the problem was somewhere in our shipping process said kuh 
she would not say who the culprits were 
we are certain that the majority of students in india did not 
have preknowledge of the test questions said kuh 
nonetheless because it is etss responsibility to provide valid 
test scores ets must cancel all scores in group security cases 
when it is impossible to determine which scores are valid and which 
are not 
</TEXT>
