<TEXT>
the following dispatch was written before the 
writer along with other western correspondents was expelled late 
sunday from lithuania 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the standard photograph of soviet 
founder vladimir i lenin found in the office of every factory 
manager has vanished leaving a telltale patch on the wall over the 
desk of vincas babilius 
i had all the books too babilius said pointing to bare 
shelves that once held the works of lenin and karl marx but since 
lithuania declared independence on march 11 babilius no longer 
feels compelled to follow the soviet model to run the vilnius 
electrical measuring device factory 
while lithuanias political leaders struggle daily with moscows 
effort to make them renounce the declaration of independence 
people all over the small baltic nation are quietly moving to 
establish a state run on its own principles 
they have an enormous task lithuanias telephone and 
connections to the outside world go through moscow its sole direct 
route to poland and the outside world is a tiny back road so 
overused that passing through frontier formalities can require 
days it is caught in a web of connections to the soviet economy 
which is rapidly careenng downhill 
babilius knows it will take years to untangle the mess left by 
50 years of communism 
but he has begun already he has banned the political meetings 
that consumed staff time and helped ensure communist grip on power 
at work you have to work he said simply 
on the lithuanianbyelorussian border the new government so far 
has been unable to station frontier guards because of the angry 
reaction from moscow 
but some enterprising citizens have lopped off the 
russianlanguage half of a huge concrete sign at the village of 
sumskas and left it lying in the dirt theyve repainted the 
remaining half to say lithuanian republic and dropped the 
soviet socialist that used to fall in the middle of the name 
the culture ministry is gathering artists designs for a 
lithuanian currency and banker romualdas visokavicius has already 
sought printing bids in west germany 
the newspaper sovietskaya litva or soviet lithuania has 
changed its name to eko litva or echo of lithuania control has 
been transferred from the communist party to the government 
an enterprising printer has stamped restoration of the 
lithuanian republic over the wording on a decorative vilnius 
envelope even though it still carries a 5kopeck soviet stamp 
on a recent sunny spring day workers chipped at the parliament 
building to remove a row of soviet emblems embedded in the front 
wall a few yards away over the front door a modern batik in the 
lithuanian colors of yellow green and red depicts an ancient 
lithuanian knight on horseback three weeks ago it too identified 
this as a seat of soviet power 
but building a new nation is much more than surface changes and 
lithuanians are just beginning that part of the task 
a raft of economic reforms is already drafted harvard economics 
professor larry summers has written a plan for switching to a 
market economy that calls for swift price reform and introduction 
of an independent currency by next year 
another american adviser new york lawyer william hough of the 
firm walter conston alexander amp green has been writing appeals 
to foreign governments for formal recognition 
ive been trying to get them to adopt the delaware commercial 
code he said the other day 
adoption of this standard would give lithuania a set of rules 
for a market economy simply and quickly he argued and it would 
encourage foreign investment 
at one stroke thousands of companies and lawyers around the 
world would understand exactly what their law is hough said 
hough said hed been doing some of his work at the lithuanian 
foreign ministry an elegant but nearly empty shell that he found 
a perfect example of the hollowness of the soviet unions claim 
that lithuanian was sovereign while part of the soviet union 
they dont even have a library he said 
the republic is already partially on its way to its own airline 
air lithuania doesnt have its name on a single plane but months 
ago it leased the entire aeroflot operation serving lithuania said 
gintautas preidis the groups banker 
such leasing operations are a key part of soviet president 
mikhail s gorbachevs own economic reforms and the lithuanians 
have already taken advantage of it to start up direct flights from 
vilnius to east berlin and leipzig frankfurt is next 
some lithuanians already had passports issued by their 
stillfunctioning embassies abroad most west european governments 
honor the passports because they never recognized soviet 
annexation 
but soviet kgb troops still control lithuanian borders so even 
emissaries of the new government had to use their red soviet 
passports to get out of the country 
when the soviets barred foreign correspondents lithuanian 
foreign minister algirdas saudargas met british correspondent 
edward lucas as he walked off the onceaweek flight from east 
berlin right before the stunned face of a soviet border guard 
saudargas issued him a lithuanian visa numbered vt0001 it 
included stamps of both independent and soviet lithuania 
the attempt didnt last long lucas was forced to leave sunday 
with the rest of the foreign press corps 
the lithuanians were forced to readopt their 1938 constitution 
which is not nearly democratic enough for most activists this was 
done it in part to establish legal continuity with the independent 
lithuanian nation that existed before soviet occupation and 
annexation in 1940 
but the lithuanians didnt have a new constitution written 
either 
</TEXT>
