<TEXT>
leon trotsky resisted vladimir ilyich lenins 
offers to become the soviet revolutionary leaders successor 
because he feared his jewish origins would hurt the communist 
cause according to a new historical study 
soviet historian victor danilov says a document has come to 
light that contains trotskys only known explanation for turning 
down lenins offers of high office 
writing in history workshop a journal published by oxford 
university press danilov cites what he says is a hitherto 
unpublished speech trotsky made at a congress of senior soviet 
communists held oct 2527 1923 
trotsky was lenins partner in leading the 1917 revolution but 
now lenin was ill and josef stalin and his supporters were 
maneuvering to oust trotsky from the leadership 
defending himself to the congress against charges that he lusted 
for power trotsky sought to demonstrate how he consistently shied 
away from high office danilov wrote 
the fact is comrades that there is one personal aspect of my 
work which although playing no role in my personal life and my 
daytoday existence is nonetheless of great political 
significance this is my jewish origin trotsky was quoted as 
saying 
i clearly remember vladimir ilyich stretched out on the floor 
in the smolny his leningrad headquarters on 25 october 1917 and 
saying to me we must make you peoples commissar of the interior 
comrade trotsky you shall crush the bourgeoisie and the 
aristocracy 
and i refused i said that in my opinion there was no point in 
playing into the hands of our enemies it would be far better i 
said if there was not a single jew in the first soviet 
revolutionary government stuff and nonsense vladimir ilyich 
said thats all rubbish however my words evidently had their 
effect for i was not appointed commissar of the interior but of 
foreign policy although to be honest i was equally loth to 
accept this post 
according to the speech trotsky also was reluctant to take on 
the post of war commissar and i was right remember how at 
critical moments of the yudenich kolchak and wrangel military 
campaigns our enemies were able to exploit the fact that the red 
army was headed by a jew this was a very great inconvenience to 
us 
trotsky was born lev davidovich bronstein into a middleclass 
russian jewish family trotsky was an alias he assumed while on the 
run from czarist authorities 
he was quoted as saying in the speech that lenin thought his 
preoccupation with being jewish was merely a personal whim of 
mine and frequently referred to it as such in conversations with 
me and other comrades 
when lenin offered to make him his sole deputy in effect lining 
him up as an heir apparent i firmly turned down his offer on the 
grounds as before that we should not give our enemies the 
opportunity to say that our country was being ruled by a jew i 
think vladimir ilyich agreed with me although he again said 
stuff and nonsense i felt that he said it this time with less 
conviction and that privately he agreed with me 
danilov wrote that trotskys speech was recorded in summary by 
stalins assistant b bazhanov and came to light only now when 
the soviet policy of glasnost is allowing historians to enter 
onceforbidden areas 
danilov wrote there was no reason to distrust bazhanovs 
account so fully does it convey the sincerity and conviction of 
trotskys words and so damningly does it reflect upon the 
organizers of this kangaroo court 
lenin died a year later trotsky was expelled from the communist 
party in 1927 and transformed by stalinist propaganda into the 
archenemy of the people he went into exile and ended up in mexico 
where he was murdered in 1940 by an acquaintance described by 
trotskys friends as a stalin agent 
</TEXT>
