there are signs president fernando 
collor de mellos draconian economic measures are throwing the 
economy into recession and brazilians are desperately trying to 
weather the storm 
industrial production dropped 20 percent from february to march 
private economists say and the automobile and contruction 
industries are virtually paralyzed unions say 200000 workers have 
lost their jobs 
a recession is now inevitable what we must avoid is a 
depression said rep jose serra of the centerleft brazilian 
social democratic party 
collor de mello passed the measures by decree on march 16 the 
day after he took office as the countrys first popularly elected 
president in 29 years 
they became law immediately but can be voted down by congress 
within 30 days legislators were to begin voting on the plan monday 
but failed to obtain a quorum congressional leaders said they 
would try again today 
the economic measures designed to halt record 4000 annual 
inflation includes a 30day price freeze a new national currency 
and drastic government spending cuts 
the package also contains an 18month freeze on assets of more 
than 1200 in private savings accounts and 600 in money market 
funds 
the freeze withdrew about 115 billion from circulation or 80 
percent of bank deposits and led to a brutal drop in consumer 
spending 
restaurants movie theaters and shops have seen a radical drop 
in business 
i havent gone out to eat or to a bar since the plan was 
announced ive cut out all expenses that arent absolutely 
