continue to fish the cold salmonrich waters south of the aleutian 
islands 
the pact calls for 98 vessels from japans squid and largemesh 
driftnet fleets to be monitored in the 1990 fishing season by 47 
us 41 japanese and 10 canadian observers last year 32 japanese 
driftnet vessels were covered by observers 
the monitoring transmitters will send signals to satellites 
enabling the government to tell when the vessels enter waters where 
driftnetting is illegal critics of driftnetting say the 
mileslong nets illegally capture north americaspawned salmon and 
kill thousands of marine birds and mammals 
