<TEXT>
here is a chronology of 18yearold ryan 
whites battle with aids 
december 1984 white 13 is diagnosed as having contracted 
aids through a bloodclotting agent used to treat his hemophilia 
july 30 1985 western schools corp superintendent james o 
smith bars ryan from school smith says the health risk for other 
children is too great 
aug 3 ryan and his mother jeanne are present when the state 
board of health announces guidelines for admitting children with 
aids to school officials urge smith to allow ryan to attend class 
as long as hes not severely ill 
aug 8 the whites sue in federal court to get ryan admitted to 
school 
aug 16 us district judge james e noland says the court 
cannot accept the case until ryans attorney exhausts all 
administrative appeals 
aug 26 classes begin at western middle school ryan is linked 
to school by a computertelephone hookup 
nov 1 the indiana department of education hears testimony 
from attorneys for white and the school district 
nov 25 hearing officer kathleen madinger angelone rules ryan 
should be allowed to go to school when he is not intensely sick 
dec 17 the western school board votes to appeal angelones 
ruling 
feb 6 1986 the department of educations appeals board rules 
there is nothing to prevent ryan now 14 from attending classes if 
he receives clearance from the howard county health officer 
feb 13 dr alan adler howard county health officer 
certifies ryan fit to return to school 
feb 19 a howard county judge turns down a request by parents 
and students to bar ryan from school 
feb 21 ryan attends a halfday of school a howard county 
judge later in the day approves a temporary injunction preventing 
him from attending school 
march 12 ryans attorney charles vaughan files a motion for 
a change of venue for an additional hearing 
april 10 clinton county circuit judge jack r oneill lifts 
the injunction saying he had no evidence of a threat of 
irreparable harm to ryans classmates ryan returns to class later 
that day 
april 30 oneill dismisses arguments from parents who oppose 
ryans attending school 
june 17 oneill denies a motion by david rosselot the 
parents attorney thus blocking the first step in the appeals 
process the motion was to correct what rosselot said were errors 
in the judges decision lifting the restraining order 
july 18 the indiana court of appeals dismisses the parents 
appeal of oneills ruling rosselot announces the parents are 
abandoning their fivemonth legal battle blaming financial 
problems 
aug 25 ryan begins eighthgrade classes at western high 
school 
summer 1987 mrs white moves her family to the small community 
of cicero about 20 miles from their home saying they didnt want 
to stay where they were unwanted in cicero they are welcomed by 
the community and school system 
aug 31 ryan attends his first day of classes as a freshman at 
hamilton heights high school no protests are reported mrs white 
says ryan has been using the drug azt for two weeks and is more 
alert 
sept 29 the ryan white national fund an educational and 
fundraising program to fight misconceptions about children 
carrying the aids virus is announced in west hollywood calif it 
is endorsed by pro football players and hollywood celebrities 
march 3 1988 ryan testifies before the white house aids 
commission ryan says i came face to face with death at 13 years 
old but decided to live a normal life 
aug 18 filming begins in north carolina of the ryan white 
story an abc tv movie it airs on jan 16 1989 
june 1989 white receives a new ford mustang as a gift from a 
mysterious benefactor mrs white says she believes the gift was 
from michael jackson 
dec 6 mrs white says surgery to correct a hernia in ryan has 
been delayed because of medical problems she also says he has 
staph infections and has not attended school much during the 
semester 
dec 16 1989 ryan turns 18 in continued ill health 
march 29 1990 ryan is admitted to riley hospital for children 
suffering from a respiratory infection 
april 2 hospital officials say ryan is in critical condition 
on a lifesupport system 
</TEXT>
