a guide who helped lead a deadly climb of 
mount hood said the expedition likely would have ended safely if 
only it had been abandoned sooner in the face of a gathering storm 
ralph summers testified monday in a lawsuit brought by richard 
haeder whose 16yearold son was one of nine people to die in a 
