haeder has sued the oregon episcopal school and summers a 
parttime assistant for at least 860000 in damages he alleged 
negligence in the planning and carrying out of the climb that led 
to the freezing deaths of seven students and two adults 
summers 34 said all of the group members probably would have 
survived had they stopped climbing and turned around at the 
hogsback area near the summit of the 11237foot peak the 
secondmost climbed mountain in the world behind mount fuji 
instead the group of climbers continued its efforts to reach 
the summit in deteriorating weather and by the time it turned 
around a powerful snowstorm was lashing the mountain he testified 
the weather was worse on the descent summers testified 
the wind was much stronger it was easy to fall over and not know 
if it was because of the terrain or the wind 
the rev thomas goman was leading the climb but summers said he 
takes responsibility for all of the major decisions on the 
