<TEXT>
israel today displayed its rocket and 
technological prowess launching the ofek2 communications 
satellite the second in a series of experimental spacecraft 
the satellite is widely viewed in the arab world as a spycraft 
that will allow israel to have immediate intelligence on arab 
military moves 
the launch came one day after iraqi president saddam hussein 
threatened to use chemical weapons against israel if attacked but 
israel space agency head yuvaal neeman denied that the satellite 
had any military purpose or that the longrumored launch was in any 
way a response to the warning 
we dont send satellites because of threats he said 
neeman described the new satellite as experimental and similar 
to the ofek1 launched aboard a gray threestage rocket sept 19 
1988 
the only difference is that we can call the satellite and send 
it messages and receive answers back neeman said adding it 
is not a spy satellite and has no military significance 
witnesses said the rocket lifted off at 302 pm rising slowly 
above a ball of orange flame and leaving a zigzag trail of white 
smoke 
it was launched from an undisclosed site in the center of the 
country and entered orbit 90 minutes later 
the satellites orbit will range from 125 miles at its lowest 
point to 923 miles at its highest according to space agency 
spokesman avi sarhan 
we said at the launch of ofek 1 that there would be a whole 
line of satellites afterwards ofek 2 is just one more step a 
successful step in this program sarhan said 
he said the ofek 2 weighed 374 pounds the same as ofek1 
