the pipe 
they are trying to stabilize that soil ms deitzel said 
its a precarious situation because its saturated with fuel 
theyre out there working with lifelines 
two years ago an ashland oil tank ruptured sending 713000 
gallons of diesel fuel into the nearby monongahela river and 
affecting water supplies downtstream on the ohio river as far away 
as sistersville wva 
