<TEXT>
attorney thomas root was released on bond 
after pleading innocent to fraud and other charges tuesday in a 
case his attorney said would not be that big a deal for the 
government if root had not gained public attention last summer 
when his airplane plunged into the atlantic ocean 
root was released on 200000 bond ordered to surrender his 
passport and report semiweekly by telephone to a probation officer 
and confined to the continental united states until a trial date is 
set 
us district judge john garrett penn said he will set a trial 
date on april 23 
root was indicted march 22 on 20 counts of wire and mail fraud 
seven counts of filing false legal documents with the federal 
communications commission four counts of using counterfeit and 
altered federal documents and one count each of forgery and 
obstruction of a grand jury investigation 
the charges against the washington attorney arise out of his 
