attorney david eisenberg sought a more stringent bond requiring 
root to post 10000 
defense attorney eugene propper argued that root should be free 
on his own recognizance saying the charges were a standard white 
collar case and would not be that big a deal for the 
government if the widely publicized plane ditching had not 
occurred 
eisenberg replied it is a big deal for the government not 
