<TEXT>
during her husbands 20year rule 
imelda marcos was praised by a controlled media as the mother of 
the nation 
on tuesday the widow of former president ferdinand marcos went 
on trial in federal court in new york as an accused embezzler and 
racketeer facing up to 50 years in prison and fines up to 1 
million if convicted 
mrs marcos is accused of taking part in the illegal transfer of 
160 million from the philippines and defrauding financial 
institutions of 165 million to finance the purchase of new york 
properties saudi financier adnan khashoggi is accused of helping 
marcos died in september in hawaii where he lived since he was 
ousted four years ago in the popular uprising that propelled 
corazon aquino to the presidency 
the story of the marcoses illustrates very vividly how fame 
riches and power can build then destroy wrote the philippine 
daily inquirer it shows that wealth is no insurance for 
security peace of mind and happiness 
mrs marcos had led a fairytale life a glamorous beauty born in 
near poverty who used charm and steely determination to become one 
of the richest and most powerful women in the world 
imelda remedios visitacion romualdez was born july 2 1929 in 
manila to vicente romualdez a lawyer and his wife remedios 
although the family was prominent imeldas father failed in 
several business ventures and the family often struggled to survive 
at age 26 after romances with several prominent filipinos 
including mrs aquinos future husband benigno aquino jr imelda 
met and married marcos a rising political star 11 years her senior 
she had three children imelda or imee in 1955 ferdinand 
jr in 1958 and irene in 1960 
mrs marcos soon became her husbands indefatigable campaigner 
charming audiences with her beauty and singing when marcos was 
elected president in 1965 he credited imelda with drawing a 
million votes 
mrs marcos boasted she needed only a few hours sleep each night 
we all wake up with the same energy she once told the 
associated press but for me the moment i see beautiful flowers 
a beautiful smile a beautiful deed this energizes me so by 
the time its midnight i am just ready to take off 
as first lady her power and influence in the philippines became 
second only to that of marcos especially after he declared eight 
years of martial law in 1972 
in 1978 mrs marcos won a seat in the national assembly 
defeating aquino who campaigned from his jail cell aquino later 
went into exile in boston and was assassinated in 1983 moments 
after returning to the philippines to challenge the marcoses for 
national leadership 
marcos also named his wife presidential envoy 
plenipotentiary and she made as many as 15 trips a year to 
confer with world leaders 
mrs marcos was credited with improving relations with the 
soviet union and china negotiating oil deals with mexico and 
cooling the philippines moslem rebellion by a meeting with libyan 
leader moammar gadhafi 
she so deeply charmed cuban president fidel castro that he once 
told her admiringly my lady what is there that you cannot do 
she had a fondness for american movie stars including her close 
friend george hamilton 
as her influence grew she declared that she would commit her 
life to improving filipino culture beautifying cities and towns 
and improving the lot of the impoverished masses 
as the appointed governor of metro manila mrs marcos built a 
10 million cultural center on reclaimed land in manila bay she 
also built bridges schools hotels and hospitals 
in her post of minister of human settlements she built 
thousands of houses planted hundreds of thousands of trees and 
loaned money for smallscale livelihood projects 
critics charged mrs marcos used her trips abroad for massive 
spending sprees in fashionable boutiques she frequently flew to 
the fun spots of the world often with an entourage known as the 
blue ladies because of their dress 
</TEXT>
