calif press 20 
another survey made public in connection with the societys 
annual meeting said 14 percent of the news sources quoted on the 
front pages of 20 newspapers during one month were women a survey 
of the same papers a year ago found 11 percent of quoted sources 
were women 
the survey on the appearance of women in photos and bylines and 
as news sources on front pages was commissioned by the asne human 
resources committee and the university of south californias media 
watch women and men associated with feminist betty friedan 
it showed that womens bylines appeared on an average of 28 
percent of stories in the 10 large and 10 smaller newspapers in the 
survey last year womens bylines appeared over 27 percent of 
stories 
women were featured in 32 percent of photos this year compared 
with 24 percent last year 
editors of surveyed newspapers were asked to comment 
i am damned if i can see what conclusions should be drawn from 
your findings the wisdom of the ages appears to cry out for 
silence said ben bradlee of the washington post 
