stating his personal position of issues but he was endorsed by the 
political action committee on wisconsin right to life 
the wisconsin recall was rooted in a 1983 federal court ruling 
that said wisconsins six chippewa bands retained the right to 
fish hunt cut timber and gather food on offreservation public 
lands under 19thcentury treaties that ceded northern wisconsin to 
the us government the ruling is under appeal 
recall organizers primarily stop treaty abusewisconsin were 
especially critical of holperins support last year for a 10year 
multimilliondollar payment to the lac du flambeau chippewa in 
return for the band limiting their exercise of treaty rights the 
