<TEXT>
the soviet government tuesday turned up 
the pressure on independenceminded lithuania by restricting 
traffic at the republics border with poland 
the polish foreign ministry which announced the action said it 
was surprised by the soviet action the polish embassy in moscow 
was told to seek an urgent explanation from the soviets 
the polish foreign ministry reminds that free border traffic 
is regulated by international conventions which should be 
respected it said in a brief statement poland is ready for 
talks on this issue 
poland is the only country bordering lithuania the baltic forms 
a section of the republics western border 
soviet officials informed their polish counterparts that the 
crossing was temporarily closed tuesday morning the polish 
news agency pap said it did not say how long it would remain 
closed 
the agency said soviets and poles could continue crossing the 
border to return home 
the border crossing in the extreme northeast corner of poland 
between the polish town of ogrodniki and the lithuanian town of 
lazdijai can only be used by poles and soviet citizens 
poles sharing centuries of common history with lithuania have 
rejoiced in the republics drive to join poland in shaking off the 
soviet yoke imposed after world war ii 
after the march 11 independence declaration by lithuania polish 
officials offered vigorous support for the republics right to 
selfdetermination 
but the noncommunist polish government did not actually 
recognize the lithuanian government a move that could endanger 
relations with the soviets 
lithuania was the subject of lengthy debate monday in the 
solidarityled cabinet foreign minister krzysztof skubiszewski 
reported no change in the polish position that the requirements 
to recognize the vilnius government have not yet been met and we 
recognize the lithuanian right to statehood 
the polish reaction has been complicated by the anxiety that 
surging lithuanian nationalism has caused among the 260000 ethnic 
poles in lithuanias population of 38 million 
poland and lithuania were linked from 1386 when a lithuanian 
ruler married a polish princess until 1795 when the commonwealth 
was broken by russia 
after world war i the newly independent states of poland and 
lithuania argued over vilnius where the population was largely 
polish and jewish poland finally seized vilnius and held it until 
world war ii 
when lithuania and poland fell under soviet domination the 
polish border was moved west and the polish population largely 
uprooted vilnius is now the capital of lithuania 
polish border officials had reported reduced traffic at the 
crossing recently on sunday 4039 people and 810 vehicles used 
the crossing pap said 
the agency also said despite the closing workers with valid 
soviet visas would still be permitted across the border for their 
jobs 
it said cargo transportation and train travel were continuing 
but that bus routes had been halted 
