northern areas of the great plains still 
suffer from lack of moisture for crops and pastures but farther 
south the story was too much rain the governments joint 
agricultural weather facility said tuesday 
rain improved winter wheat condition in portions of the 
central great plains during the week of march 26april 1 the 
facility reported crop condition was mostly good in colorado and 
kansas nebraskas winter wheat was fair to good 
in the southern plains too much moisture caused some yellowing 
of the wheat crop and hampered fertilizer application the crop 
condition was said to be good to fair in oklahoma and missouri 
rain improved winter wheat in northern texas but excess moisture 
was a problem in some areas 
