positition thornburgh said there was an apparent 
misunderstanding of what my position was so i thought id better 
clear it up 
the department had stated previously that its regulations did 
not provide for turning over the results of a criminal 
investigation to opr which conducts internal probes of alleged 
impropriety by justice department lawyers 
opr has the power to conduct grand jury investigations of its 
own and to recommend that the attorney general take disciplinary 
action against specific employees 
in a march 7 letter to rep charles schumer dny chairman of 
the house criminal justice subcommittee the justice department 
said that the applicable 1980 regulation does not contemplate the 
referral of investigative findings in a mater appearing to involve 
a violation of law from the criminal division to opr 
the purpose for referring a report to opr is obviously to 
consider whether an individual whose misconduct was not serious 
enough to constitute a violation of law should nevertheless be 
subject to some disciplinary sanction said the letter by bruce 
c navarro acting assistant attorney general in charge of the 
office of legislative affairs 
consequently no further disciplinary investigation could form 
a basis upon which to consider disciplinary action navarro 
wrote forwarding the report of the investigation to opr would 
thus not serve any purpose 
