under current law new car fleets all models produced in a 
year by one manufacturer are required to average 275 miles per 
gallon the bryan bill would require manufacturers to improve their 
average fuel economy by 20 percent beginning with the 1995 model 
year and 40 percent by the 2001 model year 
the typical new car fleet would average 344 mpg in 1995 and 
402 mpg by 2001 although some would be higher and some lower 
because the increase would be based on improving the mileage from a 
makers current level 
