parliament on tuesday adopted legislation 
for free elections and unanimously voted petar mladenov who 
initiated democratic reforms in bulgaria to a newly created 
presidency 
the ruling communists also renamed their disgraced party the 
bulgarian socialist party in an apparent effort to distance 
themselves from their hardline past and decades of unpopular rule 
in bulgaria 
the legislation for multiparty elections scheduled this june 
sets the terms for the first free balloting in bulgaria since world 
war ii 
the legislation was agreed to last week following three months 
of tough talks between the communists and the opposition and was 
ratified by parliament along with constitutional amendments 
abolishing all references to communist and socialist 
both the communists and the opposition agreed last friday to 
mladenovs election to the new presidency 
