british officials trying to limit the upheaval 
caused by its unpopular new local government tax on tuesday 
ordered the 20 highestspending authorities to impose lower taxes 
and cut budgets 
the move came in the aftermath of violence in central london on 
saturday night after a rally against the socalled poll tax turned 
into a mob riot through the capitals west end 
environment secretary chris patten set the topspending 
authorities a 28day deadline to reduce the tax for this fiscal 
year if they refuse patten will impose the cuts 
it is deplorable that local authorities have chosen to budget 
at these levels putting an unacceptable burden on the local 
people patten told the house of commons it is little wonder 
that strong feelings have been expressed up and down the country 
