anonymous callers to local news media said the medellin cartel 
kidnapped estrada and would release him soon with a message for the 
government 
otalora said estrada had opposed traffickers attempts to 
persuade the government to open peace talks with them 
last week the medellin cartel threatened to resume killing 
government officials judges policemen and the owners of 
colombias second largest newspaper el espectador of bogota 
on tuesday the morning daily said in a frontpage statement it 
would suspend its entire editorial column until the government 
gives the paper adequate protection 
the editorial column often filled with denunciations of 
traffickers was a strip of blank white paper two columns wide and 
12 inches long 
the medellin cartel killed el espectadors publisher guillermo 
cano in a submachinegun attack in 1987 in the last four months 
six el espectador employees have been killed by traffickers hit 
squads 
more than 200 people have been killed in bombings and other 
terrorist attacks since the latest government crackdown began in 
august when drug lords killed a leading presidential candidate 
el tiempo newspaper said the new suspects to be extradited 
include jacobo marino mendez a congressman for the northern state 
of magdalena he is wanted by a puerto rican court on charges of 
distributing marijuana in us territory 
