city that inspired the film american graffiti risk fines under 
a pair of ordinances that won final approval on tuesday 
under the new rules which take effect may 5 motorists would 
face fines of 75 to 250 for passing a designated checkpoint more 
than once every four hours pedestrians gathered in parking lots 
and along sidewalks would risk equal fines for loitering between 6 
pm and 6 am 
officers will enforce the rules within a marked nocruising zone 
on the popular mchenry avenue when traffic moves slower than 5 mph 
or intersections are blocked 
the ordinances do not affect the annual graffiti night which 
celebrates the cruising tradition in grand proportions with up to 
100000 people in 30000 cars 
the rules were sought by residents and business owners who 
complained that the goodnatured pastime of the 1950s had grown 
unmanageable with the influence of drugs gangs and vandalism 
but the rite of passage was defended by teenagers who grew up 
