<TEXT>
a meandering flow of molten lava from 
kilauea volcano had residents of this coastal community packing 
their belongings tuesday and preparing to leave 
a flow from the west the most serious threat advanced within 
50 yards of five homes in the kalapana gardens subdivision 
according to hawaii county civil defense spokesman bruce butts 
the flow moved 200 yards during a 12hour period ending early 
tuesday butts said the flow picked up speed by midmorning 
residents of 50 of the 125 homes in kalapana gardens evacuated 
monday and an order affecting seven more homes was issued later 
tuesday butts said 
many residents were stoic about the encroaching lava drinking 
beer and laughing with friends while watching the molten earth edge 
toward their homes 
morale is really high were just sticking together said 
craig heiser who built his home in 1987 
its a little like a party atmosphere he said you cant 
do anything about it so you might as well enjoy it 
people who live here are emotionally prepared for it but you 
still hope its not going to happen said donna olson whose home 
was destroyed in the 1986 flow and lives with her three children in 
a rented house threatened by the west flow 
what else can you do this is the hawaiian style of doing 
things i just want to get it over with said julie beardsley 
who lives in one of the five homes immediately threatened 
another flow on the eastern side of the community was moving 
toward the subdivision along the path of a 1989 flow and was about 
a halfmile from nearest homes butts said 
some of the residents hired container trucks to carry their 
belongings away many others were packing in anticipation of an 
eventual evacuation order 
i ran into a couple of people who didnt seem too concerned 
about it but most people are concerned and moving whatever they 
can said civil defense spokesman allen parker 
civil defense administrator harry kim also ordered the kalapana 
area closed to tourists and other visitors 
scientists said about 650000 cubic yards of lava was being 
pumped out of the volcanos kupaianaha vent each day 
tom wright chief scientist at the hawaiian volcano observatory 
said the lava began spreading over the slope a week ago 
now it has gathered itself into a couple of significant 
flows he said 
wright said that based on the topography of the area the two 
flows could join and send a single stream of molten lava into 
kalapana gardens 
since the east rift zone eruption began on jan 3 1983 76 
dwellings and a national park visitor center have been destroyed 
causing more than 20 million in damage 
kilauea volcano is near the southeast coast on the island of 
hawaii which is about 200 miles from honolulu on the island of 
oahu 
