<TEXT>
carlo testi remembers when the problem of 
illegal immigration came to his door right on the via de 
calzaioli one of the most fashionable streets in this renaissance 
city 
a few african immigrants spread blankets on the pedestrian mall 
putting out sunglasses and fake louis vuitton bags for sale others 
came and soon there were 400 vendors 
people couldnt pass any more testi said gazing down the 
street from his familys centuryold hat shop to the ponte vecchio 
a 14th century bridge it was a desperate situation 
these days not an african vendor is in sight city hall sent 
hundreds of police to round up illegal immigrants and vendors 
newspapers called it a witchhunt for blacks 
the police sweep which followed a bloody attack by youths on 
african immigrants raised an outcry and made florence the 
birthplace of renaissance humanism the symbol of a national debate 
on immigration and racism 
italy has given the world 26 million emigrants deputy 
premier claudio martelli said is it possible that the fifth or 
sixth industrial power loses its bearings is torn apart or reacts 
with furor and malice before the difficulties and problems raised 
by a few hundred thousand immigrants 
violence against immigrants has been a problem in central and 
northern european countries as they have absorbed citizens of 
former colonies and workers from poorer countries france 
experienced a wave of racist attacks on north africans in recent 
weeks 
florences immigrants are poor africans and latin americans 
attracted to countries in southern europe that have enjoyed 
economic booms but still lack the immigration controls imposed in 
recent years by france britain and scandinavia 
experts say italy with about 100000 illegal immigrants 
arriving each year has become the focal point of the new 
migration it has difficulty absorbing them despite a strong 
economy because of scarce housing and poor public health and 
education systems 
this ethnically homogeneous country has seen ugly racial attacks 
in recent years that many italians had thought occurred only in the 
united states or at least outside italy 
the government now hopes to stem the immigration with an 
amnesty its second in four years 
immigration in the past year has been huge and unforeseen 
said giorgio morales a socialist who was forced to resign as mayor 
of florence after the police sweep 
these new phenomena have come in a short time in florence and 
because of this there has been a reaction of intolerance he said 
estimates of the number of illegal immigrants in italy range 
from 500000 to 15 million 
ugo vittorio saibante of the governments national council of 
the economy and work said he believed the number was about 1 
million up 100 percent from 1985 and that only about half had 
work permits 
authorities say many illegal immigrants take jobs italians no 
longer want particularly in the countryside where they pick 
tomatoes help fishermen or work in small factories 
saibante however spoke of a tendency among people from less 
developed countries to go to the cities where there are many 
fewer possibilities here is where the problems of racism begin 
trouble developed in florence about a year ago as african 
vendors filled the streets around the pinkandgreen duomo 
cathedral and the 14th century city hall the palazzo vecchio 
which attract thousands of tourists daily 
police ignored the newcomers at first but strictly regulated 
souvenir and handicraft vendors were furious shopkeepers also 
complained 
to see all these people here in the center wasnt good for 
tourism testi said the image was ugly 
african vendors say they merely wanted to earn a living while 
looking for steady work and accuse the shopkeepers of racism 
we must sell to pay the hotel said a 26yearold senegalese 
who shares a cheap room with another vendor otherwise we have to 
sleep on the street 
in february about 4000 residents held a march of defenseless 
citizens against a crime wave many people attributed to 
immigrants working for italianrun drug and prostitution rings 
days later dozens of masked young avengers armed with 
baseball bats and iron bars went on a rampage during prelent 
carnival celebrations beating up african immigrants 
in midmarch spurred by citizen complaints authorities ordered 
the largescale police operation to pick up illegal immigrants and 
chase african vendors away the vendors responded with a hunger and 
sitdown strike 
the assault by youths and massive police action shocked 
italians who are proud of their tolerance and have a long emigrant 
tradition other racist attacks have taken place in major cities 
people also yelled crook swindler invader at my father in 
boston monsignor luigi di liego rome director of the charity 
organization caritas said in an interview in the newspaper la 
repubblica 
officials hope to ease tensions with a new amnesty law sponsored 
by deputy premier martelli a socialist 
it would allow foreigners who arrived before dec 31 to get work 
permits and benefits unlike an unsuccessful 1987 amnesty the new 
law imposes heavy penalties on employers who do not legalize their 
workers and establishes strict rules about who can enter the 
country 
critics predict it will not slow the flood of immigrants who 
often come by sea and do not pass through border controls 
with the amnesty italy has sent a message whoever enters 
this country not only will never be thrown out but sooner or later 
will be regularized said giorgio la malfa head of the 
republican party part of the governing coalition his party 
opposed the amnesty measure in parliament 
</TEXT>
