disappointments 
however the natural robert redfords allegorical movie in 
1984 about a gifted player and bull durham 1988 an amusing 
and lusty tale of the minor leagues starring kevin costner and 
susan sarandon helped turn things around 
the biggest grossing baseball movie of all time is last years 
field of dreams which had taken in 533 million by august 
bull durham was second with 503 million and the comedy 
smash major league 1989 ran third with 485 million all 
three are on video 
