faster than most human ears can pick up theres little of 
costellos bitterness however as this couplet suggests if 
theres a nuclear winter at least it will snow 
the cassette has 15 songs and many of them are crackling good 
there are slower moments such as the uninspired folkie duet with 
peter case things snowball and other cuts buried on side 2 
but harding has an unexpectedly high batting average on this 
audacious debut 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 
pale columbia toad the wet sprocket 
 
toad the wet sprockets new album pale exemplifies 
everything thats wrong about the wheezing alternative rock scene 
far from the cutting edge the underground scene has too many 
imitators instead of innovators the reigning gods are still 
rem which methodically built a successful career with 
originality and relentless work 
since the early 1980s rem has had more impersonators than 
elvis presley toad the wet sprocket is only the latest to emulate 
the form rather than the substance of rem 
pale is loaded with moody slightly incongruous lyrics the 
guitar rock mixes the jangle and the drone the covers a grainy 
picture of something indistinguishable and the band photo is blurry 
sound familiar 
admittedly the failure of an entire genre is a tough burden to 
place on the shoulders of an unassuming california rock band 
theyre somewhat adept interpreters the sound is more muscular 
than murmur era rem though the songs of course lack 
distinctiveness 
but it would be far better to see bands try to make their mark 
with their own visions rather than someone elses 
