in 1936 the photographer walker evans worked with author james 
agee in hale county ala preparing an article on sharecropping 
that later became their book let us now praise famous men 
1941 
artist williams christenberry was greatly influenced by the book 
as a university of alabama graduate student in 1960 and he began 
photographing hale county buildings and countryside primarily as 
studies for his paintings 
evans and christenberry met in 1961 and returned to hale county 
together in 1973 
photographs the two artists made in hale county over a 50year 
period will be on display at the amon carter museum in fort worth 
texas from april 27 to june 24 
following its run at the amon carter of time and place 
walker evans and williams christenberry will travel to the 
wichita art museum kansas dec 1 1990jan 20 1991 the 
portland museum of art maine feb 17april 14 1991 and the 
friends of photography san francisco july 2sept 9 1991 
