<TEXT>
on her emergence as a film director sondra 
locke makes an observation about gender 
women have to work twice as hard to be taken seriously she 
said from my experience what i had to fight against was my 
association with clint eastwood because it automatically 
disqualified me in some ways as being a separate entity or having 
had to fight on my own i was doing things before i met clint 
you have to fight harder people dont stop and think how long 
you have been around or what you may be on your own there is a 
wall but if you just know who you are and keep plugging along 
sooner or later the little crack in the wall gets bigger pretty 
soon you can put your foot through then you are able to emerge as 
yourself 
with her second film as a director impulse sondra locke 
does emerge as a filmmaker who can be taken seriously unlike her 
first effort the largely unseen ratboy impulse has the 
elements for popular appeal its a cop movie with theresa russell 
as an undercover vice officer who can be as tough as dirty harry 
the comparison to clint eastwood movies is unavoidable but miss 
lockes long professional and personal association with eastwood 
having reached a bitter ending she is making strides in 
establishing her own life and career 
breaking up was hard to do for both parties over 13 years she 
had appeared in six eastwood films from the outlaw josey wales 
to the gauntlet and they were close companions despite her 
marriage to another man they parted amid acrimony in december 
1988 and last april she filed a palimony suit alleging cruel 
treatment by eastwood it is still pending 
locke established her own fame in her first movie the heart 
is a lonely hunter winning a 1968 academy award nomination as 
supporting actress when she was only 17 
her discovery by hollywood is so clicheladen that its hard 
to believe 
its like a movie bigger than life she admitted but 
its actually true i was this girl in shelby tennessee i wanted 
to be an actress but was just out of school and didnt know how to 
go about it 
suddenly warner bros is having this talent search and the 
casting director marion dougherty is going from city to city the 
nearest city was birmingham ala i read about it in the paper i 
auditioned the next thing i knew i was in new york then i was in 
selma ala shooting with alan arkin 
the next thing i knew i was in hollywood and then i was 
nominated for an academy award it was an amazing experience 
enough to confuse the brain 
more films followed run shadow run willard then the 
association with eastwood during those years she remained in the 
shadow of a superstar subordinating her own ambitions how does 
that reconcile with her strong feelings about a womans role in 
society 
ive thought about that a great deal she said we go 
through certain phases in our lives we grow and change and get 
different perspectives for a time i thought that the only thing 
that can be counted on is your work you know exactly what you can 
do and you have control over it to some degree 
thats not right either a relationship is very important 
sometimes that is how we find out about ourselves from the breakup 
of a relationship we find out even more hopefully we can turn 
that into creativity if we try hard 
for a period in my life a relationship was the most important 
thing everything else was just very very secondary theres 
no doubt that professionally i did go into a tunnel then it can be 
exhilarating and challenging and exciting to try to come out of 
it 
at 42 sondra locke has the same willowy blond beauty that she 
displayed as the 14yearold mike kelly in the heart is a lonely 
hunter dont be fooled by her seeming fragility on a movie set 
she can be commanding and decisive for impulse she prowled the 
mean streets of los angeles with a homicide squad to soak up how 
the police operate 
and she scorns any suggestion that women cannot direct action 
the thing that posed the challenge in my mind was not the 
action per se she said when i think about action i only 
think about what happens i see it in my head as a movie i dont 
stop and say ooo this is action if you tell the story of 
whats happening it kind of takes care of itself 
are the wounds of the eastwood affair beginning to heal 
i think ive learned a lot she said hesitantly im proud 
of that i had to be a lot stronger than i ever knew that i could 
be i had to learn to stand up for myself and decide who i am what 
i need and whats right if you look on that as a positive instead 
of a negative then i would say that yes i am healing 
</TEXT>
