<TEXT>
clint black has one regret about being 
the hottest emerging country music star of 1990 
i dont get to fish much anymore the 28yearold singer 
says 
theres little time to head for a lake and cast for a big one 
for the past year hes been crisscrossing the country on a 
whirlwind schedule as the most promising country performer since 
randy travis blossomed in 1986 
his debut album killin time sold 1 million copies in nine 
months three cuts from the lp all were no 1 on the country music 
popularity charts a better man killin time and 
nobodys home 
im spoiled rotten he jokes about his quick success 
how is he handling it 
with a bullwhip 
its not just blacks voice that has caught the fancy of country 
fans its also his looks he has a friendly face accented by 
dimples and a mischievous grin and with his omnipresent black 
cowboy hat many people believe he looks like a young roy rogers 
he has the familiar background of a dirttodiamonds country 
singer he was born in long branch nj where his father had a 
temporary job working on a pipe line he grew up in houston where 
he was a frequent sight on the streets riding a skateboard while 
playing a harmonica he first performed for guests at his parents 
backyard barbecues 
he dropped out of high school in houston and toiled as an 
ironworker and fishing guide he sang in nightclubs after sending 
out fliers to advertise his performances he finally drew the 
attention of rca records which signed him to a recording contract 
but he hasnt forgotten his hardscrabble days 
i think about it all the time he said theres always 
something that takes me back to that i used to sing five hours a 
night sometimes seven iron working was hard and dangerous enough 
to run me off but it all shaped my life 
his album which has been no 1 on the country charts is mostly 
wellcrafted country weepers about lost love with a background of 
beers and barrooms the music much of which he wrote himself is 
rooted in the western swing and honkytonk style of texas 
the cut killin time deals with drinking to forget a broken 
romance a better man is about recovering from the pain of 
losing a lover nobodys home is about the emotional letdown 
after failing at love 
the first thing a country music listener latches onto is 
whether the words mean anything to them black says you need 
to be able to say something anybody can relate to 
nobodys home was written after a sevenyear splitup i had 
regrets we got back together and split up again this inspired a 
better man other than that the songs are just somebody elses 
story we took their perspective 
his music and tireless work have paid off rapidly in october 
he won the horizon award from the country music association for 
achievement by a rising performer in january he won an american 
music award for favorite new country artist 
hes performed at carnegie hall in new york city and he was 
especially thrilled to sing for a crowd of 56000 in houston in 
february it was etched in my mind for a long time since it was a 
hometown show and everything he said 
his future schedule is packed hell tape a bob hope tv special 
in acapulco mexico hell be on the road an average of four nights 
a week doing concerts with the superstar group alabama hes 
working on a second album due out this fall 
its satisfying to make it through a crazy week he said 
the only frustration i have is if i cant perform because my 
vocal chords are worn out from too much use 
ive been careful to shape my attitude i travel with my band 
and we hold nothing back if anyone gets out of line we answer to 
each other we pay attention to what we do and how we act 
i dont want to be a temperamental artist the band lets me 
know if im being unreasonable about something i want to make sure 
people are proud to be with me 10 years down the road 
i really have believed in my songs i feel i know when they 
are good or just ok its pretty scary to think that theres got to 
come a time when a song wont be number one its inevitable 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

