<TEXT>
general motors corp president robert c stempel 
who today was named to succeed roger b smith as gm chairman rose 
through the companys product ranks a path decidedly different 
from that of his predecessor 
stempel will take over operation of the worlds largest 
corporation aug 1 the day after smith retires as gms 10th 
chairman and less than three weeks after stempel turns 57 
stempel a big man who peers directly at whomever hes talking 
to has been the companys president and chief operating officer 
since sept 1 1987 during months of speculation about smiths 
successor stempel was given the inside track 
but that wasnt because his background mirrored smiths in auto 
industry parlance stempel is a product guy and smith is a 
bean counter 
stempel received a bachelors degree in mechanical engineering 
from worcester polytechnic institute in massachusetts in 1955 and a 
masters degree in business administration from michigan state 
university in 1970 
smith gms chairman since jan 1 1981 received bachelors and 
masters degrees in business administration from the university of 
michigan he joined gm as a senior accounting clerk in detroit 
stempel joined gm as a senior detailer in the chassis design 
department of the companys oldsmobile division in 1958 the same 
year smith became director of the general accounting section in the 
detroit central office 
each man climbed through the ranks in the 1960s with stempel 
concentrating in powertrain design and smith focusing on corporate 
finances 
in 1972 stempel was named assistant chief engineer at 
oldsmobile and smith was named vice president and group executive 
in charge of the nonautomotive and defense group 
stempel joined the legion of nearly four dozen gm vice 
presidents when he became general manager of the companys pontiac 
division in 1978 two years before going to europe to head the 
automakers adam opel ag carmaking operation in west germany 
gms european operations have produced profits that helped the 
giant automaker last year regain the top profit spot it lost to 
ford motor co in 1986 
during the speculation about smiths successor auto analysts 
said among the best things gms board could do to slow or reverse 
the companys slide in us market share is elect someone who could 
apply the lessons learned in europe to the companys worldwide 
operations 
in 1982 stempel returned to the united states to head the 
chevrolet division the companys largest carmaking operation two 
years later he was named executive in charge of the 
buickoldsmobilecadillac group 
in february 1986 stempel joined smith on gms board of 
directors as executive vice president in charge of the worldwide 
truck amp bus group and the overseas group 
nineteen months later he became gms 17th president 
