at least one aspect of trade talks between the 
united states and japan is reassuring in some respects that is 
each nation proposes moves that conceivably could help the other 
why should there be resistance over that maybe there shouldnt 
be but there is trade talks like all internation discussions 
become mixed up in politics not to mention diplomatic nuances 
the japanese would like to see americans cut the budget deficit 
save more raise the skills and overall abilities of workers put 
more effort into longterm research and in general improve the 
quality of products 
media reports suggest other maybe more controversial proposals 
have been made including a reduction in credit cards lower 
corporate bonuses and higher gasoline taxes all ideas with support 
within the united states 
for its part the united states would like to see the japanese 
