<TEXT>
pessimism about the economy and outcome of trade 
talks with the united states have helped spur the protracted slide 
in japans stock market analysts said tuesday 
traders said many investors are concerned the the trade 
negotiations in washington could affect the structural causes of 
japans 49 billion trade surplus with the united states and lead 
to wrenching changes in an exportoriented economy that is largely 
responsible for the nations stunning growth 
in the talks called the structural impediments initiative the 
united states has pressured japan to boost public works spending 
simplify its complex distribution system ease the way for large 
retailers to open stores and tighten enforcement of its 
antimonopoly law 
japan will have to make a series of changes in the structural 
talks and will have to forget about the old structures that 
supported our stock market boom and the strong yen in the past 
said kenji maeshiro a stock analyst with yamaichi securities co 
what we need now is to have a new approach to stock investment 
in order to cope with the new economic structures and policies 
he said 
