interest rates rise stocks fall 
the bank of japan plunged in by boosting its key official 
discount rate three times from 25 percent to 425 percent 
followed by an additional 1 percentage point hike on march 25 this 
year to 525 percent the objective was to discourage borrowing 
cool inflation and stabilize the yen 
market players had expected the most recent discountrate 
increase to come shortly after parliamentary elections on feb 18 
and blamed the extended delay with further destabilizing stock 
prices and the yen 
