billion to 73496 billion the finance ministry reported monday 
the tumble was the third consecutive monthly decline 
takahashi said stocks will continue to fall unless underlying 
problems a mix of higher interest rates the weaker yen and 
higher consumer prices show signs of improvement 
the yen is unlikely to strengthen under japans current 
political and economic conditions he said 
japan has became more isolated and its relative importance has 
declined as hopes about reforms in eastern europe and uncertainties 
