futures prices of grain and soybeans closed 
mostly higher tuesday on the chicago board of trade amid 
speculative buying centered in the corn and wheat markets 
the late rally in the grains spilled over into soybean trading 
reversing a slide that had threatened to extend the sharp losses 
posted monday when soybean futures plunged as much as 11 cents a 
bushel 
