buying while commercial grain dealers were net sellers on the day 
said victor lespinasse a floor trader for dean witter reynolds inc 
he linked the rally to rumors of new soviet purchases of us 
corn and to expectations for a seasonal advance in prices as the 
1990 growing season begins 
grain and soybean futures typically rise early in the growing 
season as traders focus on weather conditions and the potential for 
crop damage 
