<TEXT>
the heads of the big three tv networks complained 
tuesday that cable television had several profitable advantages 
over them although the chief of thirdplace cbs said his company 
had no plans to develop cable ventures as the other two had 
chief executive officers thomas murphy of abc laurence tisch of 
cbs and robert wright of nbc each told the national association of 
broadcasters that one expensive factor affecting the networks was 
regulations enabling them to lock up shows for only four years 
after the fouryear period the networks end up paying huge sums 
to production studios to retain shows that had become hits 
nbc just bought a seventh year of the cosby show at a 
reported 50 million the most expensive renewal in tv history 
were in the worst of all worlds tisch said we are 
allowed to lose money if it doesnt work but not allowed to make 
any money if it does work 
with network costs soaring and advertising revenue sluggish 
while competing cable channels are reaping revenue from advertising 
and subscriber fees we have to develop other revenue streams 
wright said 
he said ratings indicate the majority of tv viewers still are 
watching the big three networks but theyre nevertheless paying 
for cable tv none of us get any of that money wright said 
broadcasters are asking congress to make cable companies pay for 
carrying broadcast television programming 
abc and nbc are in the cable tv business abc by ownership of 
espn and lifetime and nbc with its cnbc cable channel but cbs 
has no such ventures 
i think we missed the boat perhaps tisch said maybe we 
should have been in the business 10 or 12 years ago 
but i cant picture cbs developing a cable network that could 
be profitable and im not in the mood to bang my head against the 
wall for 10 years the only thing a new toy would do is assure 
that we stay in third place forever if were going to succeed 
well succeed as free broadcasters 
murphy said abc was fortunate that its cable ventures 
particularly espn were well established 
cbs meanwhile has spent billions of dollars for network sports 
programming including new contracts with major league baseball and 
the national football league 
financially its not a gamble tisch said we need the 
sports support i think the advertisers will be there 
murphy said abc did not give up on sports we got outbid we 
decided wed rather put our money on series programming 
