digital music programming over cable tv lines 
scientificatlanta inc said it will make the gear to send the 
music while international cablecasting technologies inc said it 
will provide the musical programming over 27 channels initially up 
to 288 channels could be used eventually the companies said 
the system will allow the transmission of compact discquality 
sound over a satellite network that will be hooked into local cable 
tv systems in the home the system will be attached to a 
subscribers stereo system 
the service called the digital music network is scheduled to 
be launched this fall the companies said 
telecommunications inc and viacom international inc both 
major operators of cable tv systems and prime cable another cable 
operator have signed on to offer the service to more than 5 
million subscribers said jerold h rubinstein chairman of ict 
rubinstein is a former chairman of abc records and former chairman 
and coowner of united artists records 
scientificatlanta is a major maker of cable tv selector boxes 
and satellite transmission equipment 
