carl icahn said tuesday his plan to break up 
usx corp into separate energy and steel businesses would be worth 
a third more than the companys current market value 
in a letter to other usx investors a shareholders committee led 
by the new york investor estimated the value of the plan at 48 a 
share including 39 a share for usxs marathon oil co subsidiary 
and 9 a share for its us steel unit 
usx stock closed at 3712 tuesday up 150 a share on the new 
york stock exchange icahn claimed his plan would boost shareholder 
value by 35 percent based on mondays closing stock price of 
3562 a share 
icahn who owns 1329 percent of usx or about 34 million 
shares has asked the companys 144000 shareholders to approve a 
plan to spin off at least 80 percent of us steel to existing 
shareholders with the remaining 20 percent going to new investors 
the spinoff company would assume no more than 15 billion of the 
steel divisions longterm debt 
usx management has opposed the plan saying it would make 
marathon and us steel more vulnerable to slumps in either the 
energy or steel industries usx bought marathon in the early 1980s 
as a cushion against cyclical swings in the steel business 
usx has said 65 percent of its revenues come from marathon 
while 31 percent come from steel operations 
icahn said in the letter that usx could properly structure the 
breakup to make it essentially taxfree to the company and its 
stockholders the plan would preserve net operating losses of usx 
he said 
usx chairman charles corry recently told wall street analysts 
that icahns plan would cause tax difficulties because the company 
could lose tax credits resulting from steel losses in the early 
1980s 
the stockholders will cast nonbinding votes on icahns proposal 
may 7 at marathon oils headquarters in findlay ohio 
icahn the chairman of trans world airlines inc is joined on 
his stockholders committee by twa vice chairman alfred kingsley and 
mcdep associates inc chairman kurt wulff 
icahn said he based the 48ashare figure on analyses by the 
committee and by mcdep 
usx officials were not immediately available for comment tuesday 
night 
